creator: grizolle_benedicte@emc.com
text:
Created attachment 22383
Contains JUnit test class and documents used for testing.

The Office 2007 Word Template Format 'dotx' seems to be not supported.
Find in attachments the JUnit test class and the document used for testing.
We expected to extract the words "testdoc" and "test phrase".

Notes on the attached documents:

- the document "classic_TemplateDocument.dotx" contains the words  "testdoc" and "test phrase" in the template document.


"TestUnitPoi35Filter.java" is the JUnit class.

creator: yegor@dinom.ru
text:
Fixed in r795327.
The fix added support the following files:

Microsoft Office Word 2007:

    * Word 2007 template(*.dotx)
    * Word 2007 macro-enabled document (*.docm)
    * Word 2007 macro-enabled template(*.dotm)

Microsoft Office Excel 2007:

    * Excel 2007 macro-enabled workbook (*.xlsm)
    * Excel 2007 template (*.xltx)
    * Excel 2007 macro-enabled template (*.xltm)
    * Excel 2007 add-in (*.xlam)


Regards,
Yegor
